These are not decisions.
They are programmed responses.

Anything learned can be unlearned.

Lesson 3: What Nicotine Actually Does in Your Body
Nicotine enters your bloodstream in seconds.
It spikes dopamine and gives a brief hit of relief.

But the relief is fake.
Nicotine causes the discomfort it pretends to fix.

The cycle:

Nicotine enters

You feel a buzz

Nicotine level drops

You feel anxious or empty

You use nicotine again

The â€œreliefâ€ is just ending withdrawal that nicotine created.
When you stop, the cycle ends and withdrawal passes quickly.

