Youâ€™ve run this loop thousands of times.
Your brain believes the trigger requires nicotine.

Reality: triggers donâ€™t cause nicotine.
They only predict nicotine.

You break the loop by interrupting the trigger-response pattern.

Lesson 2: How Triggers Control You
Triggers arenâ€™t cravings.
Triggers are situations your brain links with nicotine.

Coffee. Driving. Meals. Stress. Breaks.
Your brain whispers: â€œThis is when we smoke.â€

That whisper is not you.
Itâ€™s the addiction protecting itself.

Lesson 3: How to Interrupt Any Craving
